happy June 🌹 it’s THE PERFECT FIND premiere month and I’m going to highlight a member of our outstanding creative team & crew every day (THE PERFECT CREW ✨) leading up to our June 23 premiere @netflix
The crew works so hard and creates so much magic. and im here to spread some recognition! Starting with Phillip Prince our location manager. For me the locations are the foundation of the film. When you step on set that location can motivate you excite you and welcome you. The communities that these locations are in also deeply matter to me as it can bring resources, jobs, and put lesser known places on the map. Here’s Phillip in my office he was often sitting here as I’d dream really big about black opulence and where could we film and create worlds that we haven’t seen before in NY/NJ 
This man came through with all the goods I know he was stressed, but he was dedicated to giving me and the film theeee very best. Our main location ended up being at the @newarkmuseumart completely transforming the space that already had incredible bones. Thank you Phillip @escarondito

The Perfect Crew ✨Look at Alyssa Longchamp @a.longchamp_ (in purple) getting the shot. My earliest art/work was centered in photography so i was excited to hire our set photographer—and when I saw Alyssa’s portfolio it was an instant yes. Her visual point of view and the way she’s always able to find the perfect moment full of emotion is a special talent. This work requires so much patience. You can’t share anything until the film comes out and that’s usually over a year from when you first worked. It’s long hours and you have to make yourself known in a seamless way to get the shot while not disrupting. Alyssa thank you —you gave us so much and now more of your gorgeous work is being seen. 🌹

our JUNE 14 NYC TRIBECA FILM FEST WORLD PREMIERE is just days away. Thank you @adesola_thomas @letterboxd for listing THE PERFECT FIND as a must see palate pleaser for auteurs and rom com lovers. Tix are available so grab yours now and see you all soon! Link in bio to purchase 💕💕💕

social_posts.post_text: continuing my spotlight on THE PERFECT CREW ✨ here we have Mike Walker Michael Walker @skywalkerfx man with the plan ! one of my best friends on set this guy is the salt of the earth —great mentor to tons of new crew -uplifting black & brown to really know how to do this job. I could go on and on. For me a good film cannot be made without a great 1st AD. Assistant Director is an odd name for this job as it goes far beyond assisting. There’s a million things that can and will go wrong or rather I should say constant changes are the name of this game. You gotta be very nimble and come up with creative solutions for every rock and pebble that gets thrown your way. While maintaining your vision 😍It’s the pebbles that are the most challenging by the way. So as the challenges would pop up especially during filming early in the pandemic 👀 I’d sit with Mike and go over what I thought we could do to save a day or location or an actor who tested + and now we gotta scramble etc. I’m going to cry thinking of a day where I came to Mike about a few things I’d be willing to sacrifice to get our budget under control and he saw me really going to the wall. He told me not to give in on everything because they’d only take more away — that’s how this monster machine of filmmaking can be — he let me know he had my back and then he showed me in action every single day. He also makes THEE best slab o ribs in the tri state area. Mike was absolutely a key partner in the making of this movie and we had a great time doing it together. Thank you Mike!!! Take all the flowers 🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹

shout out to Klarissa & Abe part of THE PERFECT CREW ✨ i love this pic. Klarissa @klaridadiva was our 2nd 2nd AD and let me tell you she was on the ground every single day making sure things went right. This is a role that is partially like an apprenticeship as you take on more and more responsibility as a second and first AD. The AD team is the secret sauce that keeps the film organized and on track and Klarissa made it very fun while under constant pressure. Thank you!!! 🌷Now next to her we have @crackedhalo_ I hate that we can’t really see each other cause we had to mask up and no one knows that more than him haha! He was part of the team keeping us from getting shut down like so many productions had to do during the earlier pandemic months. We got through it together and he’s my Haitian brother 🇭🇹 so you know we were protected all around. Much love and thank youuuuu

Let’s talk about Q! @quenelljones_soc our B cam operator member of THE PERFECT CREW & very talented photographer & DP as well. You can see in our eyes we are both smiling grinning cheesing and that was us every day on set. Q also shot the gorgeous b roll footage you’ll see in the film giving us NYC texture and a sweet train motif I can’t wait to talk about more. Q is a great guy who gave me 1000 percent support — then over a year later I go to direct the season finale of @nbcyoungrock — and who do I see? Q! Wearing our Perfect Find T shirt — 💕 gotta say that was an awesome reunion. You never know how you’re going to be received on set especially as a Black Woman. I’m the director and not everybody loves that every where ya go ya know? Guys like Q (and I’m happy I know so many) but guys like Q feel like home. Thank you for everything you gave to the film and the kindness and joy you brought 🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹

🌹bespoke🌹 filmmaker in a (fancy) frock. behind the scenes with @houseofaama who made both of my gowns for the nyc and miami premieres of THE PERFECT FIND. I had the pleasure of making a fashion film in 2020 that featured some of their collection at the time and I never forgot them. I knew one day they’d make custom work for me and lucky me they said yes AND came all the way to the east coast to dress me. Both premieres were magical nights of celebration and i felt like my very best self. Thank you @iyomihoken @shabakaaa @rebeccalouise1967 for everything!!! Thank you @stevenjamesmeidenbauer for capturing these moments and crafting this film and thank you @killahcamz @natitasnewbeginnings for the nyc makeup & French roll updo!

it’s my very happy birthday. breakfast in bed by best husband @gbrey and annual tradition watching my fave movie CATS I don’t care I love this movie so much 🐈‍⬛🐈😻
this year was one for clarity. Very clear I don’t work for freeeee thank you union strikes —very clear I’m an artist who needs to create beyond making a living —my living is art —everything I do is a reflection of my artistry— the way I light my home —the way I am with friends —with family— I care— I care alot —I care deeply —sometimes maybe snobby sometimes maybe crunk sometimes maybe strange —getting ok with the feeling of not belonging —rare ones don’t fit in but I found so much love and maybe yes finally letting it in now. happy birthday to me thank you my angels for watching me guiding me supporting me protecting me sprinkling magic upon me
